{
  "texts": [
    "The multiple predictions obtained for the same (c, g) pair across different cell lines and perturbagen types were further aggregated into a consensus target ranking, and then mapped into a probability score using an adjusted logistic regression (LR) model (see Methods), which is referred to as Model L hereafter, where L stands for L1000.",
    "A welladopted convention for comparing transcriptional models is to calculate the recall 3, 5, i.e., the percentage of compounds having their Broad-annotated known targets 42 predicted among the top N% of the candidate list, with N set to 5 here (see Methods).",
    "For comparison, we trained the same Siamese networks using gene signatures represented by other state-of-the-art gene and GO embeddings as input.",
    "The recallrank plot in Fig. 2b demonstrated a significant performance boost in our FRoGS-based model compared to other approaches.",
    "With the baseline recall value estimated to be 8.0 ± 2.7% based on 100 random permutations, CMap 1,40 and OPA2Vec GO 24 methods performed similarly to random models with recalls at 9.6% and 9.5%, respectively."
  ]
}